Member number: A number (1-8) that identifies the SMSF member. You must provide member information in relation to all current members and former members, who held an interest in the fund at any time during the year, including: - those for whom no contributions were made during the year, as well as - those for whom you are reporting a nil closing account balance. Report all current members at 30 June, regardless of their account balance. Include all members who receive an income stream payment from the SMSF who hold an interest in the fund at 30 June. Also report deceased members and all former members who left the fund during the year, for example by either rolling out their benefits or being paid a lump sum. If there are more than eight (8) current, deceased and former mebers to be reported, please contact the ATO. This is a mandatory field.

Net capital gains income: Enter the amount of Net capital gain. If the franking credit is attached to a dividend considered as non-armâ€™s length income, include the amount.
